  "why": "The paper's method, DeepEvolution, is designed and evaluated for testing a single Deep Neural Network (DNN) model at a time. The experimental evaluation focuses on finding erroneous behaviors (RQ2) and quantization defects (RQ3) within the specific model under test (LeNet for MNIST, CifarNet for CIFAR-10). The paper does not conduct experiments to demonstrate whether the fault-inducing inputs discovered for one model also cause failures in other, independently trained models designed for the same task. The comparison between a model and its quantized version in RQ3 is not considered transferability in the context of this metric, which focuses on independently trained models. Therefore, the paper does not demonstrate cross-model transferability.",
